All right, I'll give you an example code for a basic webpage with the features you requested. You can adjust the styling as desired. Here's the code:

```
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>My Webpage</title>
	<style>
		header {
			display: flex;
			justify-content: center;
			align-items: center;
			height: 50px;
			background: #333;
			color: #fff;
			font-size: 18px;
		}

		header a {
			color: #fff;
			text-decoration: none;
			margin: 0 20px;
		}

		h1 {
			text-align: center;
			margin-top: 50px;
		}
	</style>
</head>
<body>
	<header>
		<a href="#">Sign Up</a>
		<a href="#">Login</a>
		<a href="#">About Us</a>
	</header>
	<h1>Welcome to My Webpage</h1>
</body>
</html>
```

In this code, we have a `header` element containing three links, and a `h1` element as the title of the page. The `flexbox` is used to center the header items both horizontally and vertically, and the style of the links and the title can be customized as desired by modifying the CSS code.

